NATIONAL police commissioner General Khehla Sitole has ordered an immediate mobilisation of the 72-hour activation plan to hunt for suspects who shot a police officer. Sergeant Lungisile Rasmani (46) was shot in Walmer, Nelson Mandela Bay in the Eastern Cape, on Wednesday evening, 19 January. According to Lieutenant-Colonel Robert Netshiunda, it is reported that Rasmani had just finished duty and was opening the gate of his residence when he was apparently accosted by three unknown men. Netshiunda said one of them shot him in the back. “The suspects are alleged to have robbed him of his service pistol and a cellphone. Sergeant Rasmani, who is attached to Humewood Port of Entry, was rushed to hospital where he is reported to be in a critical condition,” he said. Netshiunda said cases of attempted murder and robbery with a firearm have been opened for investigation and a manhunt for the suspects is underway. Anyone with information about the whereabouts of the suspects is urged to contact the nearest police station or call CrimeStop number on 08600 10111. Alternatively, tip-offs can be relayed via the MYSAPS app.